						<div class="postbody">Yeah, no quirky attribute tables is really a big advantage on the SMS. But do you really mean what you said about Z80? I think it's a big mess, with lots of unlogical register combinations and adressing modes. It may all come to sense if you learn to use it properly, but it seems quite strange to me :/
<br />
<br />EDIT: And, also, I think SMS can display 256*224 and 256*240 (PAL only) too.</div>

